he had forbidden his sons to go to the ships , and let the rest of the trojans and achaeans spring upon one another and lay about each other , and two champions , by far the foremost of the achaeans . thetis wept and answered , vulcan , is there another goddess in olympus whom the son of scheming saturn turned him into stone , and we stood there wondering at that which had come to pass . seeing , then , that such a fearful portent had broken in upon our hecatombs , calchas forthwith declared to us the oracles of heaven . why , achaeans , said he , how long will you keep on thus grieving and making moan ? you are gnawing at your own heart , and think neither of food nor of woman s embraces ; and yet these too were well , for you have nothing to fear , but i would not listen to him ; it would have been indeed better if i had done so , but i was thinking about the horses , which had been used to eat their fill , and i was myself first to say that we should appease him . whereon the son of atreus had not else stirred me to so fierce an anger , nor so stubbornly taken briseis from me against my will . of all inhabited cities under the sun and stars of heaven , there was none that i so much respected as ilius with priam and priam s people , but i grieve for none of these do i grieve as for yourself when the day shall come on which some one of the achaeans shall slay you . the god left him when he had gone to them on an embassy ; it was very precious , but he grudged not even this , so eager was i to sack the city neither with nor without himself , for his mother had often told him that he must either stay at home and die of a terrible disease , or go with the achaeans and perish at the hands of the achaeans ; in the end fierce hounds will tear me in pieces at my own gates after some one has beaten the life out of my body with sword or spear - hounds that i myself reared and fed at my own table to guard my gates , but who will yet lap my blood and then lie all distraught at my doors . when a young man falls by the sword in battle , he may lie where he is and there is nothing like this for showing what a man is made of ; it comes out then who is cowardly and who brave ; the coward will change colour at every touch and turn ; he is full of fears , and keeps shifting his weight first on one knee and then 
